  "text": "A proper design of a fermentor for immobilization of microbial cells on a suitable solid matrix is the interest of research to find out the maximum production within a short period, involving less energy in order to achieve higher productivity at economical level. Several carrier materials like alginate, carrageenan, γ-alumina, silica gel, etc. are the common support materials used for the immobilization process [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
